A 22-year-old woman, who allegedly left her three-day-old baby girl with a street vendor at Warwick Avenue in Durban, will appear at the Durban Magistrate s Court.The mother was arrested on Thursday by the Durban Central police at Warwick Avenue and charged with neglect.&#8220;It is alleged that the suspect left her three-day-old baby girl with a street vendor at Warwick Avenue and said she will be back shortly. The woman never returned and the street vendor took the baby to the police. The baby was then taken to a place of safety where she is currently being taken care of,&#8221; said Colonel Thembeka Mbhele in a statement.KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner Major General Bheki Langa praised the members for swiftly arresting the suspect. The Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual offences Unit police will investigate this case thoroughly in making sure that the suspect will get harsher sentence if convicted,&#8221; Langa said.According to Child Line SA about 4869 have been neglected in the 2015/2016 compared to the 2014/2015 financial year where 3311 have been neglected.ISS Africa has indicated a decline in child neglect and ill treatment of children from 2431 in 2014 to 2245 in 2015.-TNA REPORTER